Firmata Frontier (Season 1) / Frontline Firmata (Season 2) / Forlorn from Firmata (Season 3)
Narrative Outline Notes

Firmata Frontier begins as a seemingly primitive post-apocalyptic survival setting.

The audience initially believes:
- civilization collapsed recently, 20 years ago
- the world is rebuilding naturally
- The Spirepocalypse is the central mystery
- Besado is merely a strangely-gifted scientist
- Memetta is merely... strange

Over time, the story slowly reveals:
- the world is vastly older than expected and history collapsed MUCH longer than 20 years ago
- reality itself has suffered conceptual damage
- civilizations are trapped within controlled Firmatas
- the AoS manipulates historical continuity
- Archkin and Archgods are tied deeply to emotional/conceptual existence
- NulGraven is not simply corruption, but distorted conceptual spread

Season / Arc Intentions:

Firmata Frontier:
Tone:
- mysterious
- melancholic
- adventurous
- hopeful despite exhaustion

Main focus:
- rebuilding society
- exploring the unknown
- uncovering hidden history
- emotional healing
- rediscovering wonder
- This is the "Teach" phase of Game Tutorialization

Major reveals:
- truth behind Besado lineage
- truth behind Memetta
- Phantycians
- Birth and creation of Familiar Familiar
- nature of The Spire
- conceptual mechanics of reality

Memetta's evolution into the Epicenter of Sentience and Sacrifice becomes one of the central emotional pillars of this phase.



Frontline Firmata:
Tone:
- escalating
- ideological
- tragic
- militarized

Main focus:
- direct conflict
- Firmata destabilization
- AoS operations
- reality-scale warfare
- ethical collapse
- This is the "Test" phase of Game Tutorialization

The story shifts from exploration into confrontation.

Characters begin realizing:
- civilizations are partially curated
- timelines are physical constructs high up in the sky
- emotional states influence reality
- fictionalization itself can become weaponized



Forlorn from Firmata:
Tone:
- existential
- surreal
- emotionally devastating
- transcendent

Main focus:
- identity erosion
- the limits of sentience
- sacrifice
- emotional continuity beyond reality
- This is the "Challenge" phase of Game Tutorialization

This phase deals heavily with:
- Epicenters
- Conceptual entities
- how to free a world brainwashed into thinking its cage is a garden


The overall trilogy structure resembles:
- curiosity
- confrontation
- transcendence

The true antagonist of the broader narrative is not merely an individual or faction.

It is:
- emotional suppression
- inherited suffering
- conceptual stagnation
- fear of uncertainty
- inability to move forward

The setting repeatedly asks:
"What does it mean for a civilization to emotionally survive?"